{
    "publish_date": "2013-08-14T13:00:44.000Z", 
    "video_length": "PT8M42S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "LARRY KOSILLA: What&#39;s\nup, guys?", 
            "dur": "0.95", 
            "start": "1.946"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;m Larry from ammonyc.com.", 
            "dur": "2.02", 
            "start": "2.896"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And one of the most common\nquestions I receive is how to", 
            "dur": "2.88", 
            "start": "4.916"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "properly touch up your\ncar&#39;s paint.", 
            "dur": "2.28", 
            "start": "7.796"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In this episode, we&#39;ll discuss\nhow to resolve chip damage", 
            "dur": "2.76", 
            "start": "10.076"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "caused by dings and rocks.", 
            "dur": "1.78", 
            "start": "12.836"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In addition to resolving the\nunsightly chip marks, touch-up", 
            "dur": "2.89", 
            "start": "14.616"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "primarily protects the paint\nfrom future corrosion.", 
            "dur": "2.255", 
            "start": "17.506"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That&#39;s all coming up today on\nthis episode of &quot;DRIVE CLEAN.&quot;", 
            "dur": "3.649", 
            "start": "19.761"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[MUSIC PLAYING]", 
            "dur": "2.49", 
            "start": "23.41"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "LARRY KOSILLA: Detailing cars is\na very visual skill that I", 
            "dur": "2.684", 
            "start": "46.732"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "learned by watching talented\nartists in", 
            "dur": "1.84", 
            "start": "49.416"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "their respective fields.", 
            "dur": "1.29", 
            "start": "51.256"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Our industry has several methods\nfor touching up cars.", 
            "dur": "3.07", 
            "start": "52.546"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Some techniques work better\nthan others, and some", 
            "dur": "2.1", 
            "start": "55.616"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "professionals and weekend\nwarriors are more precise and", 
            "dur": "3.06", 
            "start": "57.716"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "patient than others when it\ncomes to the application.", 
            "dur": "2.64", 
            "start": "60.776"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "As you can see on the hood of\nmy car, the previous owner", 
            "dur": "2.49", 
            "start": "63.416"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "should be commended for taking\ntime to touch up the rock", 
            "dur": "2.58", 
            "start": "65.906"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "chips, but the result wasn&#39;t", 
            "dur": "1.42", 
            "start": "68.486"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "necessarily visually beautiful.", 
            "dur": "1.88", 
            "start": "69.906"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Today I&#39;m going to walk you\nthrough the methods I&#39;m most", 
            "dur": "1.88", 
            "start": "71.786"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "comfortable using.", 
            "dur": "1.08", 
            "start": "73.666"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The process typically takes a\ncouple of days from start to", 
            "dur": "2.55", 
            "start": "74.746"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "finish, so patience\nis required.", 
            "dur": "2.41", 
            "start": "77.296"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It involves four steps--", 
            "dur": "1.39", 
            "start": "79.706"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "assessing, prepping, application\nand leveling.", 
            "dur": "4.11", 
            "start": "81.096"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But before we get started,\nhere&#39;s what you need--", 
            "dur": "2.34", 
            "start": "85.206"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "touch-up sticks, 2000 grit\nsandpaper, Carnauba wax,", 
            "dur": "4.5", 
            "start": "87.546"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "rubbing alcohol, microfiber\ntowel, heat gun, No.", 
            "dur": "4.52", 
            "start": "92.046"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "2 pencils, Crazy Glue, color\ncoat and clear coat, touch-up", 
            "dur": "4.69", 
            "start": "96.566"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "paint and hole punch.", 
            "dur": "3.51", 
            "start": "101.256"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Step one is assessing the\ndamage to determine the", 
            "dur": "2.58", 
            "start": "104.766"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "severity of the impact.", 
            "dur": "1.76", 
            "start": "107.346"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Does it need touch-up, or will\nwet sanding be enough?", 
            "dur": "3.3", 
            "start": "109.106"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Proper touch-up is a long and\nsometimes tedious process.", 
            "dur": "3.42", 
            "start": "112.406"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And if the impact can be\nrepaired by simply wet", 
            "dur": "2.32", 
            "start": "115.826"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "sanding, I would avoid using\ntouch-up if at all possible.", 
            "dur": "4.63", 
            "start": "118.146"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Since these two areas are\nmissing clear-coat paint and", 
            "dur": "3.08", 
            "start": "122.776"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "bare metal is exposed, touch-up\nis our only option.", 
            "dur": "3.82", 
            "start": "125.856"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "First I circle the area with a\npaint pen to help find the", 
            "dur": "2.93", 
            "start": "129.676"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "small chip quickly and to show\nyou the viewers at home where", 
            "dur": "3.24", 
            "start": "132.606"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we&#39;re working.", 
            "dur": "1.25", 
            "start": "135.846"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Next, it&#39;s important to clean\nout the jagged and loose edges", 
            "dur": "3.11", 
            "start": "139.546"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of the existing chip\nfor two reasons.", 
            "dur": "3.39", 
            "start": "142.656"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The first one is you don&#39;t\nwant to put touch-up over", 
            "dur": "2.35", 
            "start": "146.046"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "unsecure paint, because\nit&#39;ll simply fall off,", 
            "dur": "2.67", 
            "start": "148.396"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "defeating the purpose.", 
            "dur": "0.99", 
            "start": "151.066"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s much like scraping flaky\npaint off an old house before", 
            "dur": "3.79", 
            "start": "152.056"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the painting process begins.", 
            "dur": "2.59", 
            "start": "155.846"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The second is that by scuffing\nup the bottom of the chip, the", 
            "dur": "3.38", 
            "start": "158.436"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "touch-up that you will soon\napply will have better", 
            "dur": "2.43", 
            "start": "161.816"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "adhesion because it&#39;s not a\nsmooth, slippery surface.", 
            "dur": "4.6", 
            "start": "164.246"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "To do this, you&#39;ll need a pencil\nwith an unused eraser,", 
            "dur": "3.21", 
            "start": "168.846"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "one 2000 grit sandpaper,\nand a hole punch.", 
            "dur": "3.85", 
            "start": "172.056"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Cut out one piece of sandpaper\nand remove it from the hole", 
            "dur": "3.03", 
            "start": "175.906"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "punch reservoir.", 
            "dur": "1.93", 
            "start": "178.936"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This tiny perfect circle sits\natop the pencil&#39;s eraser with", 
            "dur": "3.42", 
            "start": "180.866"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a drop of Crazy Glue.", 
            "dur": "1.92", 
            "start": "184.286"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Be sure to affix the\nsandpaper with the", 
            "dur": "1.97", 
            "start": "186.206"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "gritty side facing outwards.", 
            "dur": "1.675", 
            "start": "188.176"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The purpose of this trick is to\nonly scuff up the chip and", 
            "dur": "3.67", 
            "start": "192.806"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "not the surrounding area, if\npossible, because we only want", 
            "dur": "3.25", 
            "start": "196.476"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "touch-up within the\nchip itself.", 
            "dur": "3.75", 
            "start": "199.726"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The number one reason why\ntouch-up has a tendency to", 
            "dur": "2.73", 
            "start": "203.476"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "look bad is because it overflows\ninto the surrounding", 
            "dur": "3.62", 
            "start": "206.206"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "areas that don&#39;t actually need\nit, causing an uneven or bumpy", 
            "dur": "4.08", 
            "start": "209.826"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "texture that is obvious\nto the eye.", 
            "dur": "3.26", 
            "start": "213.906"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "However, the pencil trick\nfocuses the repair precisely", 
            "dur": "3.36", 
            "start": "217.166"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "where it&#39;s needed most.", 
            "dur": "1.25", 
            "start": "220.526"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The next step is a technique\nI&#39;ve used for years to help", 
            "dur": "2.89", 
            "start": "225.226"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "corral the touch-up paint into\nthe scratch and to avoid the", 
            "dur": "3.51", 
            "start": "228.116"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "non-chipped areas.", 
            "dur": "2.3", 
            "start": "231.626"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "First, add a light layer of\nCarnauba wax over the entire", 
            "dur": "3.32", 
            "start": "233.926"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "area, including the chip.", 
            "dur": "2.54", 
            "start": "237.246"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Next, use rubbing alcohol on a\ntouch-up stick to clean out or", 
            "dur": "3.74", 
            "start": "239.786"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "remove the wax from the chip.", 
            "dur": "2.8", 
            "start": "243.526"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You may need to do this several\ntimes to ensure no", 
            "dur": "2.45", 
            "start": "246.326"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "waxes remain on the exposed\nbare metal.", 
            "dur": "4.23", 
            "start": "248.776"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The reason we do this is because\nany waxed surface will", 
            "dur": "3.13", 
            "start": "253.006"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "not allow touch-ups to stick\nto it, which helps us avoid", 
            "dur": "3.25", 
            "start": "256.136"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the number one cause of bad\ntouch-up jobs, and that, of", 
            "dur": "2.78", 
            "start": "259.386"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "course, is having touch-up\nin the wrong area.", 
            "dur": "3.61", 
            "start": "262.166"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It also helps with the cleanup\nprocess, because misplaced", 
            "dur": "2.93", 
            "start": "265.776"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "drips can be wiped\naway easily.", 
            "dur": "1.65", 
            "start": "268.706"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now that the chip is clean and\nready to accept the touch-up,", 
            "dur": "2.99", 
            "start": "277.696"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we need to mix the paint and\nclear-coat prior to the", 
            "dur": "2.96", 
            "start": "280.686"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "application.", 
            "dur": "2.68", 
            "start": "283.646"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Add an even amount of color\nand clear-coat.", 
            "dur": "2.09", 
            "start": "286.326"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Then mix in a small cup until\nit becomes slightly thicker,", 
            "dur": "3.32", 
            "start": "288.416"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or more viscous than water, but\nless viscous than syrup.", 
            "dur": "4.81", 
            "start": "291.736"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This can be very tricky, because\nthere&#39;s usually an", 
            "dur": "2.57", 
            "start": "296.546"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "optimal 10 to 20-minute window\nof time before the paint", 
            "dur": "3.5", 
            "start": "299.116"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "becomes too clumpy.", 
            "dur": "1.55", 
            "start": "302.616"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, traditionally, color-coat\nwas added, dried, then", 
            "dur": "3.85", 
            "start": "304.166"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "clear-coat was added\non top afterwards.", 
            "dur": "2.75", 
            "start": "308.016"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But from a practical standpoint,\nthis is not as", 
            "dur": "2.57", 
            "start": "310.766"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "effective if your goal is to\nhave it look good as well.", 
            "dur": "3.62", 
            "start": "313.336"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I prefer to mix the color-coat\nand the clear-coat together", 
            "dur": "3.11", 
            "start": "316.956"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "prior to adding it to the chip,\nbecause it&#39;s a healthy", 
            "dur": "2.98", 
            "start": "320.066"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "balance between protection,\nlooks, and ease of", 
            "dur": "2.83", 
            "start": "323.046"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "application.", 
            "dur": "1.25", 
            "start": "325.876"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "To apply this new mixture of\npaint and clear, I remove the", 
            "dur": "3.14", 
            "start": "332.786"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "fibers from the touch-up stick\nso that it&#39;s bare plastic.", 
            "dur": "3.35", 
            "start": "335.926"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You can use a razor blade or\nsimply bite off the end.", 
            "dur": "3.67", 
            "start": "339.276"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Next, dip the touch-up stick\ninto the paint so that there&#39;s", 
            "dur": "3.04", 
            "start": "342.946"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a small collection\nat the very tip.", 
            "dur": "2.38", 
            "start": "345.986"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Your goal is to allow the paint\nto flow into the chip", 
            "dur": "3.15", 
            "start": "348.366"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and to fill up the\ncavity slowly.", 
            "dur": "2.64", 
            "start": "351.516"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The most common misconception\nis that a", 
            "dur": "2.29", 
            "start": "354.156"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "painting motion is needed.", 
            "dur": "1.76", 
            "start": "356.446"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s best to actually dab and\npush the paint around to help", 
            "dur": "3.52", 
            "start": "358.206"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it settle into the chip.", 
            "dur": "2.13", 
            "start": "361.726"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "To speed up the drying process,\nuse a heat gun on low", 
            "dur": "3.25", 
            "start": "363.856"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "for two to three minutes.", 
            "dur": "1.55", 
            "start": "367.106"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Keep touching the panel to make\nsure it doesn&#39;t get too", 
            "dur": "2.31", 
            "start": "368.656"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "hot during this process.", 
            "dur": "2.27", 
            "start": "370.966"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "As the touch-up dries, it will\nshrink, so additional layers", 
            "dur": "3.2", 
            "start": "373.236"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of paint will most\nlikely be needed.", 
            "dur": "2.15", 
            "start": "376.436"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This will take time, a\nsteady hand, and a", 
            "dur": "2.02", 
            "start": "378.586"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "good deal of patience.", 
            "dur": "2.7", 
            "start": "380.606"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Next, wet sand the area with\n2500 grit to blend the", 
            "dur": "3.56", 
            "start": "383.306"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "surrounding paint, and notice if\nit needs additional layers", 
            "dur": "2.87", 
            "start": "386.866"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of touch-up.", 
            "dur": "1.25", 
            "start": "389.736"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Use even pressure with a foam\nor rubber sanding block.", 
            "dur": "3.45", 
            "start": "393.886"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This process will help expose\nanything you may have missed", 
            "dur": "3.35", 
            "start": "397.336"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "during the original touch up.", 
            "dur": "1.445", 
            "start": "400.686"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "To remove the wet sand marks,\nI&#39;m using a microfiber cutting", 
            "dur": "2.92", 
            "start": "406.776"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "pad, leveling fluid, and a\n3-inch Rupes polisher.", 
            "dur": "3.3", 
            "start": "409.696"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Our goal is to see if we filled\nin the chip or if it", 
            "dur": "2.9", 
            "start": "412.996"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "needs additional layers.", 
            "dur": "3.55", 
            "start": "415.896"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, as expected, more touch-up\nis needed to build up", 
            "dur": "3.05", 
            "start": "419.446"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the layers within the chip until\nit&#39;s perfectly flat.", 
            "dur": "4.97", 
            "start": "422.496"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Repeat this process until you&#39;re\ncompletely satisfied.", 
            "dur": "2.49", 
            "start": "427.466"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The touch-up process can take\none hour or one week,", 
            "dur": "3.09", 
            "start": "434.816"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "depending on your tools,\nskills, and level of", 
            "dur": "3.01", 
            "start": "437.906"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "perfection required for\nyou to be satisfied.", 
            "dur": "2.185", 
            "start": "440.916"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The very last step, of course,\nis to wax your car for", 
            "dur": "2.66", 
            "start": "446.906"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "additional protection.", 
            "dur": "1.1", 
            "start": "449.566"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But always keep in the back of\nyour mind that touch-up is", 
            "dur": "2.97", 
            "start": "450.666"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "designed to help prevent\npremature corrosion and with a", 
            "dur": "3.33", 
            "start": "453.636"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "bit of patience can make it\nlook much better, too.", 
            "dur": "4.07", 
            "start": "456.966"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The small chips on the front\nof my car have been filled,", 
            "dur": "2.36", 
            "start": "461.036"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "leveled and polished, all for\nsignificantly less money than", 
            "dur": "2.91", 
            "start": "463.396"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "if I had repainted it, and\nI&#39;m feeling pretty good.", 
            "dur": "2.51", 
            "start": "466.306"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "For a PDF download of our\nstep-by-step tips on how to", 
            "dur": "2.63", 
            "start": "468.816"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "touch up your paint, be sure\nto visit ammonyc.com.", 
            "dur": "2.91", 
            "start": "471.446"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, that&#39;s if for me, guys.", 
            "dur": "1.07", 
            "start": "474.356"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Thanks again for watching\nanother episode of &quot;DRIVE", 
            "dur": "2.07", 
            "start": "475.426"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "CLEAN&quot; right here on\nthe DRIVE network.", 
            "dur": "1.6", 
            "start": "477.496"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "-Like this, and rip this\nthing off, right?", 
            "dur": "1.946", 
            "start": "482.596"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OK, good.", 
            "dur": "3.451", 
            "start": "484.542"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "See how it came off?", 
            "dur": "1.479", 
            "start": "487.993"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "-Yeah, that&#39;s great.", 
            "dur": "1.972", 
            "start": "489.472"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[INAUDIBLE]", 
            "dur": "1.479", 
            "start": "491.444"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "put it in your mouth\nand bite it off.", 
            "dur": "3.451", 
            "start": "492.923"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "-I have to put it in my\nmouth and bite it off?", 
            "dur": "1.972", 
            "start": "496.374"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "-All right, hang on.", 
            "dur": "0.986", 
            "start": "498.346"
        }, 
        {
